%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20has%20raised%20the%20possibility%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-did-russia-invade-ukraine-putin-politics-motive-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussia's%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%2C%20at%20least%20temporarily%2C%20end%2C%20as%20he%20has%20repeatedly%20pledged%20to%20resolve%20the%20conflict%20quickly%20through%20negotiations.%20He%20has%20threatened%20Russia%20with%20new%20economic%20penalties%2C%20but%20he%20has%20also%20been%20very%20critical%20of%20US%20aid%20to%20Ukraine.%20Some%20assistance%20has%20already%20been%20cut.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESupporting%20Ukraine%20is%20considered%20by%20many%20Western%20countries%20as%20a%20way%20to%20weaken%20Russia's%20military%20and%20to%20stop%20it%20from%20attacking%20elsewhere%20in%20Europe%20or%20NATO%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fputin-threatens-war-with-west-nato-expels-uk-diplomats-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eas%20it%20has%20threatened%20to%20do%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHertling%20said%20that%2C%20given%20Russia's%20situation%20at%20the%20moment%2C%20%26quot%3Bthis%20is%20by%20far%20the%20worst%20time%20to%20take%20away%20support%20from%20the%20Ukrainians.%26quot%3B%20He%20explained%20that%20he%20supported%20efforts%20to%20end%20the%20conflict%20but%20not%20by%20ending%20support%20for%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20time%20right%20now%20to%20continue%20to%20put%20pressure%20on%20the%20Russian%20government%20and%20Mr.%20Putin%20specifically%20and%20end%20this%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c0bda625-5241-4128-9c29-17c23df9ab60%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETime%20for%20a%20show%20of%20strength%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20world%20leaders%20have%20said%20that%20unrelenting%20support%20for%20Ukraine%20and%20strength%20are%20needed%20to%20end